NGUYEN TRUNG THANG is an Intern/Fresher AI/Machine Learning Engineer with no commercial experience, focusing on advanced academic projects. Their core expertise lies in Deep Learning, Machine Learning, Computer Vision, and Generative AI, with hands-on experience in Text Error Correction, Visual Question Answering (VQA), and Optical Character Recognition (OCR). They have successfully trained and fine-tuned state-of-the-art models such as ViT5 and BartPho in PyTorch for Vietnamese text correction, demonstrating strong performance through iterative optimization. Furthermore, they developed an end-to-end VQA system utilizing Generative AI for dataset creation, integrating custom CNN-LSTM-Attention models, and leveraging BLIP and Gemini API for automated image captioning and question-answer generation. Their project work also includes building an OCR pipeline combining CNNs for robust feature extraction with Transformer Decoders for sequence modeling, improving text recognition from structured documents like invoices using TensorFlow and PyTorch.
Technically, NGUYEN TRUNG THANG is proficient in Python, C, Java, JavaScript, PHP, and SQL. They possess practical experience with leading AI/ML frameworks and libraries including PyTorch, TensorFlow, Keras, Scikit-learn, HuggingFace Transformers, OpenCV, Pandas, NumPy, and Matplotlib. Their toolkit includes Linux, Google Colab for development, and GitHub for version control. They are familiar with various architectural models such as CNN, LSTM, Attention mechanisms, Transformer Decoders, and advanced models like ViT5, BartPho, BLIP, and Gemini, applying techniques like Feature Extraction, Sequence Modeling, Model Design, Training, Evaluation, Optimization, and Fine-tuning across their projects.